abstract: A gunman opened fire at the Molson Coors Beverage Co brewing complex in Milwaukee on Wednesday, killing five co-workers before he was found dead from an apparently self-inflicted gunshot wound, the city's police chief said.

abstract: President Donald Trump faces a critical personal challenge in grappling with the new coronavirus outbreak: asking Americans to believe him after he and some of his top advisers have contradicted federal scientists in playing down the threat.

abstract: Do the primaries suggest that Democrats should be sick of being reasonable?
snippet: Do the primaries suggest that Democrats should be sick of being reasonable?
lead_paragraph: According to Gallup, some 47 percent of American adults identify as Democrats or lean Democratic, which translates to roughly 10 million more supporters than the Republican Party has. Political scientists rate the national mood as the most liberal it has been since the early 1960s.

abstract: Democratic presidential contenders are describing the federal infectious-disease bureaucracy as rudderless and ill-prepared for the coronavirus threat because of budget cuts and ham-handed leadership by President Donald Trump. That’s a distorted picture. For starters, Trump hasn’t succeeded in cutting the budget.
snippet: Democratic presidential contenders are describing the federal infectious-disease bureaucracy as rudderless and ill-prepared for the coronavirus threat because of budget cuts and ham-handed leadership by President Donald Trump. That’s a distorted p...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Democratic presidential contenders are describing the federal infectious-disease bureaucracy as rudderless and ill-prepared for the coronavirus threat because of budget cuts and ham-handed leadership by President Donald Trump. That’s a distorted picture. For starters, Trump hasn’t succeeded in cutting the budget.

abstract: CBS News faced an ill-timed blow to its reputation on Wednesday following a bruising Democratic presidential debate that its moderators struggled to keep from spiraling out of control, although it could take some comfort in the numbers.
snippet: CBS News faced an ill-timed blow to its reputation on Wednesday following a bruising Democratic presidential debate that its moderators struggled to keep from spiraling out of control, although it could take some comfort in the numbers.
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — CBS News faced an ill-timed blow to its reputation on Wednesday following a bruising Democratic presidential debate that its moderators struggled to keep from spiraling out of control, although it could take some comfort in the numbers.
headline_main: Rough Debate Performance by Moderators a Blow to CBS News

abstract: The Bloomberg campaign is putting out more memes on private Instagram accounts — and running faster than Facebook can keep up.
snippet: The Bloomberg campaign is putting out more memes on private Instagram accounts — and running faster than Facebook can keep up.
lead_paragraph: Several high-profile Instagram accounts posted sponsored content for Michael Bloomberg’s presidential campaign on Wednesday afternoon.

abstract: U.S. renewable fuel prices rose 25% on Wednesday, traders said, after a Bloomberg report stated that the Trump administration has decided to pare exemptions for oil refineries from the nation's biofuel blending laws.
snippet: U.S. renewable fuel prices rose 25% on Wednesday, traders said, after a Bloomberg report stated that the Trump administration has decided to pare exemptions for oil refineries from the nation's biofuel blending laws.
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — U.S. renewable fuel prices rose 25% on Wednesday, traders said, after a Bloomberg report stated that the Trump administration has decided to pare exemptions for oil refineries from the nation's biofuel blending laws.
headline_main: U.S. Renewable Fuel Prices Climb 25% After Report on Small Refinery Waiver Program
headline_print_headline: U.S. Renewable Fuel Prices Climb 25% After Report on Small Refinery Waiver Program

abstract: Speaker Nancy Pelosi on Wednesday urged party unity amid Bernie Sanders' surge in the presidential race, even as House Democrats worry about a volatile election season that could put a self-described democratic socialist atop the ticket and threaten their majority.
snippet: Speaker Nancy Pelosi on Wednesday urged party unity amid Bernie Sanders' surge in the presidential race, even as House Democrats worry about a volatile election season that could put a self-described democratic socialist atop the ticket and threat...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Speaker Nancy Pelosi on Wednesday urged party unity amid Bernie Sanders' surge in the presidential race, even as House Democrats worry about a volatile election season that could put a self-described democratic socialist atop the ticket and threaten their majority.
headline_main: Pelosi Urges Democratic Unity Amid Sanders' Campaign Surge

abstract: The lawsuit concerns an essay published a year ago and headlined “The Real Trump-Russia Quid Pro Quo.”
snippet: The lawsuit concerns an essay published a year ago and headlined “The Real Trump-Russia Quid Pro Quo.”
lead_paragraph: President Trump’s re-election campaign sued The New York Times for libel on Wednesday, alleging that an Op-Ed article published by the newspaper falsely asserted a “quid pro quo” between Russian officials and Mr. Trump’s 2016 campaign.
